This paper deals with representation learning on heterogeneous networks, which involves both structural information and unstructured semantic content. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Databases (cs.DB).
